)Attr
 $ type(output) caps(off)
 # type(output) hilite(reverse) color(turq) caps(off)
)Body Expand(\\)
+zigihelp \-\#zigtitle   +-\-\ zigihelp
%Command ===>_zcmd
+
%Create+will execute a 'git init' in the specified path creating a%Local
%Repository. A basic .gitattributes will be commited to this repository.
+Set %ignore qualifiers+to the amount of hlq's your want to %chop off+
+the datasets inside the %Local Repository+.
+
%Clone+will clone a%Remote Repository+and then create a set of z/OS Datasets
+based on the%files+and%folders+from the remote repository (optionally prefixed
+with your%PREFIX+.
+Requires access to the remote repository via public key.
+
%Local Repository+is the location where the%Clone+will create a directory or
+where%Create+will initilialize the git repo.
+
%PREFIX+is a set of high level qualifiers (0,n) that will be prefixed
+to the Datasets from the remote repository. This%does not+change the names
+of the files and folders in OMVS.
+
\ \Press%Enter+to continue or%F3+to return to the dialog\ \
)Init
)Proc
 &zcont = zigihr0
)end
